    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-15T03:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-15T03:35:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A14/702: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-15T12:00:00+03:25"
                            >September 15, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 15—9:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Commenting upon instruction No. 39<note n="59" xml:id="d403fn59">Not printed;
                        it contained a copy of the memorandum by the Secretary of State of a
                        conversation with the Persian Minister, August 9, <ref target="#pg_469">p.
                            469</ref>.</note> Chief of the Third Political Division stated that
                    failure on the part of the American Government to follow lead of the Senate
                    would result in important repercussions in the cordial relations now existing
                    between the two countries. In view of this threat suggest objectionable
                    reservation be not approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hornibrook</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
